headline.main: Air Power Wins Again; It Is Giving Japan Her Philippine Success and Has Enabled Russia to Storm Crimea

lead_paragraph: As General Douglas MacArthur's thin line of defenders, without air support, pitifully outnumbered and outgunned, commenced their last stand at the close approaches to Manila yesterday, the indomitable Russians apparently clinched their most difficult victory of the war.
abstract: H W Baldwin on air power importance
